<h3 id="admin-for-the-client">Admin for the Client</h3>

<p>Jekyll is super easy to build and deploy for a developer but what about Pierre updating his releases going forward? Enter Siteleaf - a solution that gives a standard web based admin interface for static sites.</p>

<p>Setting things up is as simple as connecting to a repo and then Siteleaf can understand Front matter fields to give a slick UI for the administrator.</p>
